    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_"><text styleclass="Heading3_atocs_" translate="true">Where is the Base-Part Geometry?</text></para>
    <list id="148" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Why is there not a </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">CAD-Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-BasePart" styleclass="Element" translate="true">Base-Part</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">?</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">We do not want you to </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">automatically</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> add Joints to the Origin, X-axis or Y–axis of the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> (and Mechanism Axes).</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo2" translate="true">However, you are welcome to do this.</text></para>
    <list id="149" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">Why?</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">For the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">, we have found it to be useful to add </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Points</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Lines</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> that are </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">not</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> at the Origin or along the X-axis or Y–axis. We then add dimensions to give the position of the Points and Lines relative to the origin of the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <list id="150" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="3" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">Why?</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">You can </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">edit</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> the dimensions later, and also add them to a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-DesignSet" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Design-Set</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <list id="151" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">Why edit </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Points</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Lines</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> in the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Base-Parts</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">?</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">You have the design flexibility to:</text></para>
    <list id="152" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">Move the Joints, if the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Points</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Lines</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> are used for Joints</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">Move the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Plane</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">Mechanism-Editor</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> in the Machine Frame, if a </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Line</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> is used for a new </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Plane</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true"> and then </text><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">Mechanism-Editor</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">.</text></li>
